{"id":"1409.5596","submitter":"Manuel Calixto","authors":"M. Calixto, E. Romera and R. del Real","title":"Parity-symmetry-adapted coherent states and entanglement in quantum\n  phase transitions of vibron models","comments":"8 pages, 7 figures","journal-ref":"J. Phys. A: Math. Theor. 45 (2012) 365301","doi":"10.1088/1751-8113/45/36/365301","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We propose coherent (`Schr\\\"odinger catlike') states adapted to the parity\nsymmetry providing a remarkable variational description of the ground and first\nexcited states of vibron models for finite-($N$)-size molecules. Vibron models\nundergo a quantum shape phase transition (from linear to bent) at a critical\nvalue $\\xi_c$ of a control parameter. These trial cat states reveal a sudden\nincrease of vibration-rotation entanglement linear ($L$) and von Neumann ($S$)\nentropies from zero to $L^{(N)}_{\\rm cat}(\\xi)\\simeq 1-{2}/{\\sqrt{\\pi N}}$ [to\nbe compared with $L^{(N)}_{\\rm max.}(\\xi)=1-{1}/{(N+1)}$] and $S^{(N)}_{\\rm\ncat}(\\xi)\\simeq \\frac{1}{2} \\log_2(N+1)$, respectively, above the critical\npoint, $\\xi>\\xi_c$, in agreement with exact numerical calculations. We also\ncompute inverse participation ratios, for which these cat states capture a\nsudden delocalization of the ground state wave packet across the critical\npoint. Analytic expressions for entanglement entropies and inverse\nparticipation ratios of variational states, as functions of $N$ and $\\xi$, are\ngiven in terms of hypergeometric functions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 19 Sep 2014 10:56:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-22"}
